Text.Value: Attack.
Tsk'va! Where did you -

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* Can use CINE anims, i.e CINE_Startled. <LoganP>
EditorData.NodeContext: Tsk'va pronounced tsk-VA - means "shit" - the gith are surprised here

Text.Value: Captain Voss won't be happy you killed the person who found your lost weapon.
Wait! A nautiloid crashed on your doorstep. People are getting infected by mind flayers. I need help.
Wait. First, report to our Kith'rak, she might have need of you.
I have the weapon Captain Voss was looking for.
Kith'rak Voss said you're looking for a weapon, I've brought it with me.
Unlikely. Htak'a!
Do you have no mercy?
I have not transformed yet, and it's been ages. Your medics would find me useful.
Wait! I've been infected by an illithid, and I need your help.
'Mercy' is a weakness we do not suffer from.
Attack.
Let me past. It'll save both of us time and you a lot of blood.
Perhaps you could be of use to her. Seek her within.
You would ask us for help?
Kith'rak Therezzyn is similarly concerned.
There is no greater honour than bleeding for Vlaakith.
An understandable longing. Report to our Kith'rak within, she may have use for you.
Cr√®che Y'llek welcomes you, ra'stil.
Quite possible.  Enter then, and report to the infirmary. Do not stray, Cr√®che Y'llek watches you.
Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith. Enter and report to Kith'rak Therezzyn.

EditorData.NodeContext: pronounced 'cheh-MAR ZAL-ah VLAH-kith' (meaning 'Vlaakith's will above all')

Text.Value: Ah, you are kin. State your purpose.

EditorData.NodeContext: First part of the line is happy surprise

Text.Value: Ghaik have infected these lands. I need this cr√®che's help stopping them.
I see they're letting even istik mercenaries in these days.
Chk. We are never informed first. But if Kith'rak Voss wanted you alive, he must have had his reasons.
An illithid abomination will not step foot in this cr√®che.
Very well, enter. Seek Kith'rak Therezzyn within.
If you bring harm, she will cut you in two. Seek her within.
As stupid as you are unfortunate. Htak'a!
A ghaik parasite has infected me. Your cr√®che will offer me sanctuary, as is its mandate.
I simply seek to meet more of my kin, it has been too long.
Hah! You've a strong spirit, istik. Go, report to our captain, she might have use for you.
Lae'zel? Perhaps you could intervene?
Your corpse will be useful enough.
Took a wrong turn - I'll just be leaving.
Is that so? I had heard he had his ways, and I'm pleased that they bear the promised results.
You spoke to a silver sword - and you still live? Curious. We shall see what Kith'rak Therezzyn makes of this.
I seek no quarrel with you, kin. Go, speak with our Kith'rak, she might require your help.
Journey's over, istik. It'll be swift.

EditorData.NodeContext: Moving from the initial surprise to the Gith aggression/authority

Text.Value: Report to the infirmary. Ghustil Stornugoss will see to you.
I must speak with your ghustil. Our queen's protocol demands it.
Captain Voss told me to find the item you've been searching for. I have it.

Synopsis: The guards can be convinced to let you in if you are Gith-looking or have obtained the insignia.
